The fuel price is set to rise by 82 cents a litre and diesel will cost between 85 and 87c/l more from 6 June. JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Energy has announced that the fuel price is set to rise by 82 cents a litre and diesel will cost between 85 and 87c/l more from 6 June. The wholesale price of illuminating paraffin will rise by 82c/l, while the retail price of LPG will increase by 138c/kg. Last month the fuel price rose by 49 cents and diesel cost between 58 and 59c/l. The wholesale price of illuminating paraffin rose by 69c/l, while the retail price of LPG increased by 70c/kg. More to follow.